The paper deals with lower and upper bounds on tensor rank, which is a topic in computational complexity theory and linear algebra. Specifically, the paper explores the implications of tensor rank for algebraic circuit/formula lower bounds, which falls under the category of computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also constructs explicit tensors and explores their properties, which involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses representation theory and interpolation to derive upper bounds on the rank of certain tensors, which involves techniques from numerical analysis (cs.NA).
